{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1674,"text":"A little over 100 years ago, in 1915,"},{"time":6038,"text":"Einstein published\nhis theory of general relativity,"},{"time":9770,"text":"which is sort of a strange name,"},{"time":12028,"text":"but it's a theory that explains gravity."},{"time":15395,"text":"It states that mass -- all matter,\nthe planets -- attracts mass,"},{"time":19737,"text":"not because of an instantaneous force,\nas Newton claimed,"},{"time":24375,"text":"but because all matter --\nall of us, all the planets --"},{"time":28362,"text":"wrinkles the flexible fabric\nof space-time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33128,"text":"Space-time is this thing in which we live\nand that connects us all."},{"time":37905,"text":"It's like when we lie down on a mattress\nand distort its contour."},{"time":43938,"text":"The masses move -- again,\nnot according to Newton's laws,"},{"time":48894,"text":"but because they see\nthis space-time curvature"},{"time":52825,"text":"and follow the little curves,"},{"time":55672,"text":"just like when our bedmate\nnestles up to us"},{"time":59260,"text":"because of the mattress curvature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61596,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":64841,"text":"A year later, in 1916,"},{"time":67809,"text":"Einstein derived from his theory"},{"time":72224,"text":"that gravitational waves existed,"},{"time":76061,"text":"and that these waves were produced\nwhen masses move,"},{"time":79220,"text":"like, for example, when two stars\nrevolve around one another"},{"time":84049,"text":"and create folds in space-time\nwhich carry energy from the system,"},{"time":89033,"text":"and the stars move toward each other."},{"time":92148,"text":"However, he also estimated"},{"time":95103,"text":"that these effects were so minute,"},{"time":99879,"text":"that it would never be possible\nto measure them."},{"time":103323,"text":"I'm going to tell you the story of how,"},{"time":105653,"text":"with the work of hundreds of scientists\nworking in many countries"},{"time":112137,"text":"over the course of many decades,"},{"time":113947,"text":"just recently, in 2015,"},{"time":117580,"text":"we discovered those gravitational\nwaves for the first time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123542,"text":"It's a rather long story."},{"time":126598,"text":"It started 1.3 billion years ago."},{"time":133017,"text":"A long, long time ago,"},{"time":135574,"text":"in a galaxy far, far away --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":138789,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":140606,"text":"two black holes were revolving\naround one another --"},{"time":146249,"text":"\"dancing the tango,\" I like to say."},{"time":149161,"text":"It started slowly,"},{"time":150736,"text":"but as they emitted gravitational waves,"},{"time":153862,"text":"they grew closer together,\naccelerating in speed,"},{"time":156825,"text":"until, when they were revolving\nat almost the speed of light,"},{"time":160448,"text":"they fused into a single black hole"},{"time":163667,"text":"that had 60 times the mass of the Sun,"},{"time":167325,"text":"but compressed\ninto the space of 360 kilometers."},{"time":171851,"text":"That's the size of the state of Louisiana,"},{"time":174886,"text":"where I live."},{"time":176669,"text":"This incredible effect\nproduced gravitational waves"},{"time":182289,"text":"that carried the news of this cosmic hug\nto the rest of the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189893,"text":"It took us a long time to figure out\nthe effects of these gravitational waves,"},{"time":196827,"text":"because the way we measure them\nis by looking for effects in distances."},{"time":203590,"text":"We want to measure longitudes, distances."},{"time":206730,"text":"When these gravitational waves\npassed by Earth,"},{"time":209887,"text":"which was in 2015,"},{"time":212760,"text":"they produced changes in all distances --"},{"time":216815,"text":"the distances between all of you,\nthe distances between you and me,"},{"time":220455,"text":"our heights --"},{"time":221675,"text":"every one of us\nstretched and shrank a tiny bit."},{"time":226303,"text":"The prediction is that the effect\nis proportional to the distance."},{"time":230904,"text":"But it's very small:"},{"time":232718,"text":"even for distances much greater\nthan my slight height,"},{"time":237600,"text":"the effect is infinitesimal."},{"time":241443,"text":"For example, the distance\nbetween the Earth and the Sun"},{"time":245965,"text":"changed by one atomic diameter."},{"time":251000,"text":"How can that be measured?"},{"time":252902,"text":"How could we measure it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":256571,"text":"Fifty years ago,"},{"time":258953,"text":"some visionary physicists\nat Caltech and MIT --"},{"time":263181,"text":"Kip Thorne, Ron Drever, Rai Weiss --"},{"time":265910,"text":"thought they could precisely\nmeasure distances"},{"time":269980,"text":"using lasers that measured\ndistances between mirrors"},{"time":275187,"text":"kilometers apart."},{"time":278478,"text":"It took many years, a lot of work\nand many scientists"},{"time":282522,"text":"to develop the technology\nand develop the ideas."},{"time":285781,"text":"And 20 years later,"},{"time":288112,"text":"almost 30 years ago,"},{"time":291164,"text":"they started to build two gravitational\nwave detectors, two interferometers,"},{"time":297201,"text":"in the United States."},{"time":299307,"text":"Each one is four kilometers long;"},{"time":303014,"text":"one is in Livingston, Louisiana,"},{"time":307636,"text":"in the middle of a beautiful forest,"},{"time":310592,"text":"and the other is in Hanford, Washington,"},{"time":314444,"text":"in the middle of the desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317094,"text":"The interferometers have lasers"},{"time":320203,"text":"that travel from the center\nthrough four kilometers in-vacuum,"},{"time":324153,"text":"are reflected in mirrors\nand then they return."},{"time":327018,"text":"We measure the difference in the distances"},{"time":329686,"text":"between this arm and this arm."},{"time":332546,"text":"These detectors are very,\nvery, very sensitive;"},{"time":336771,"text":"they're the most precise\ninstruments in the world."},{"time":341115,"text":"Why did we make two?"},{"time":342730,"text":"It's because the signals\nthat we want to measure come from space,"},{"time":348353,"text":"but the mirrors are moving all the time,"},{"time":350842,"text":"so in order to distinguish\nthe gravitational wave effects --"},{"time":354869,"text":"which are astrophysical effects\nand should show up on the two detectors --"},{"time":359237,"text":"we can distinguish them\nfrom the local effects,"},{"time":362102,"text":"which appear separately,\neither on one or the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367323,"text":"In September of 2015,"},{"time":370099,"text":"we were finishing installing\nthe second-generation technology"},{"time":375092,"text":"in the detectors,"},{"time":377333,"text":"and we still weren't at the optimal\nsensitivity that we wanted --"},{"time":381732,"text":"we're still not, even now,\ntwo years later --"},{"time":385128,"text":"but we wanted to gather data."},{"time":387679,"text":"We didn't think we'd see anything,"},{"time":389719,"text":"but we were getting ready to start\ncollecting a few months' worth of data."},{"time":393924,"text":"And then nature surprised us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397454,"text":"On September 14, 2015,"},{"time":401761,"text":"we saw, in both detectors,"},{"time":404847,"text":"a gravitational wave."},{"time":407050,"text":"In both detectors, we saw a signal"},{"time":409546,"text":"with cycles that increased\nin amplitude and frequency"},{"time":412582,"text":"and then go back down."},{"time":413859,"text":"And they were the same in both detectors."},{"time":417315,"text":"They were gravitational waves."},{"time":420028,"text":"And not only that --\nin decoding this type of wave,"},{"time":425249,"text":"we were able to deduce\nthat they came from black holes"},{"time":429281,"text":"fusing together to make one,"},{"time":431298,"text":"more than a billion years ago."},{"time":435613,"text":"And that was --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":436820,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444339,"text":"that was fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446994,"text":"At first, we couldn't believe it."},{"time":450497,"text":"We didn't imagine\nthis would happen until much later;"},{"time":454101,"text":"it was a surprise for all of us."},{"time":456577,"text":"It took us months to convince\nourselves that it was true,"},{"time":459282,"text":"because we didn't want to leave\nany room for error."},{"time":462818,"text":"But it was true, and to clear up any doubt"},{"time":465835,"text":"that the detectors\nreally could measure these things,"},{"time":468891,"text":"in December of that same year,"},{"time":470809,"text":"we measured another gravitational wave,"},{"time":473713,"text":"smaller than the first one."},{"time":475152,"text":"The first gravitational wave\nproduced a difference in the distance"},{"time":478989,"text":"of four-thousandths of a proton"},{"time":482651,"text":"over four kilometers."},{"time":484010,"text":"Yes, the second detection was smaller,"},{"time":486528,"text":"but still very convincing\nby our standards."},{"time":493064,"text":"Despite the fact that these are space-time\nwaves and not sound waves,"},{"time":497612,"text":"we like to put them into loudspeakers\nand listen to them."},{"time":502315,"text":"We call this \"the music of the universe.\""},{"time":505834,"text":"I'd like you to listen\nto the first two notes of that music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511102,"text":"(Chirping sound)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514448,"text":"(Chirping sound)"},{"time":516600,"text":"The second, shorter sound\nwas the last fraction of a second"},{"time":521490,"text":"of the two black holes which,"},{"time":523308,"text":"in that fraction of a second,\nemitted vast amounts of energy --"},{"time":528262,"text":"so much energy, it was like three Suns\nconverting into energy,"},{"time":534937,"text":"following that famous formula,"},{"time":536537,"text":"E = mc2."},{"time":538318,"text":"Remember that one?"},{"time":540473,"text":"We love this music so much\nwe actually dance to it."},{"time":546031,"text":"I'm going to have you listen again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550546,"text":"(Chirping sound)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":554558,"text":"(Chirping sound)"},{"time":557303,"text":"It's the music of the universe!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":559327,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":563017,"text":"People frequently ask me now:"},{"time":566163,"text":"\"What can gravitational waves\nbe used for?"},{"time":569455,"text":"And now that you've discovered them,\nwhat else is there left to do?\""},{"time":574390,"text":"What can gravitational waves\nbe used for?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578034,"text":"When they asked Borges,\n\"What is the purpose of poetry?\""},{"time":582376,"text":"he, in turn, answered,"},{"time":584241,"text":"\"What's the purpose of dawn?"},{"time":585961,"text":"What's the purpose of caresses?"},{"time":587985,"text":"What's the purpose\nof the smell of coffee?\""},{"time":590580,"text":"He answered,"},{"time":592448,"text":"\"The purpose of poetry is pleasure;\nit's for emotion, it's for living.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":599769,"text":"And understanding the universe,"},{"time":601457,"text":"this human curiosity for knowing\nhow everything works,"},{"time":605131,"text":"is similar."},{"time":607177,"text":"Since time immemorial, humanity --\nall of us, everyone, as kids --"},{"time":612660,"text":"when we look up at the sky\nfor the first time and see the stars,"},{"time":616553,"text":"we wonder,"},{"time":617740,"text":"\"What are stars?\""},{"time":619847,"text":"That curiosity is what makes us human."},{"time":623174,"text":"And that's what we do with science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627856,"text":"We like to say that gravitational waves\nnow have a purpose,"},{"time":633640,"text":"because we're opening up\na new way to explore the universe."},{"time":637847,"text":"Until now, we were able to see\nthe light of the stars"},{"time":642150,"text":"via electromagnetic waves."},{"time":645168,"text":"Now we can listen\nto the sound of the universe,"},{"time":649768,"text":"even of things that don't emit light,\nlike gravitational waves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655667,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":656955,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658131,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661556,"text":"But are they useful?"},{"time":664325,"text":"Can't we derive any technology\nfrom gravitational waves?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":669507,"text":"Yes, probably."},{"time":671040,"text":"But it will probably take a lot of time."},{"time":673652,"text":"We've developed\nthe technology to detect them,"},{"time":676340,"text":"but in terms of the waves themselves,"},{"time":678401,"text":"maybe we'll discover 100 years from now\nthat they are useful."},{"time":682685,"text":"But it takes a lot of time\nto derive technology from science,"},{"time":686763,"text":"and that's not why we do it."},{"time":688373,"text":"All technology is derived from science,"},{"time":690672,"text":"but we practice science for the enjoyment."},{"time":694640,"text":"What's left to do?"},{"time":697386,"text":"A lot."},{"time":698851,"text":"A lot; this is only the beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702613,"text":"As we make the detectors\nmore and more sensitive --"},{"time":705731,"text":"and we have lots of work to do there --"},{"time":707672,"text":"not only are we going to see\nmore black holes"},{"time":709941,"text":"and be able to catalog\nhow many there are, where they are"},{"time":714269,"text":"and how big they are,"},{"time":715865,"text":"we'll also be able to see other objects."},{"time":719296,"text":"We'll see neutron stars fuse\nand turn into black holes."},{"time":724913,"text":"We'll see a black holes being born."},{"time":727536,"text":"We'll be able to see\nrotating stars in our galaxy"},{"time":730698,"text":"produce sinusoidal waves."},{"time":732930,"text":"We'll be able to see\nexplosions of supernovas in our galaxy."},{"time":738792,"text":"We'll be seeing\na whole spectrum of new sources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743641,"text":"We like to say"},{"time":745637,"text":"that we've added a new sense\nto the human body:"},{"time":749262,"text":"now, in addition to seeing,"},{"time":750984,"text":"we're able to hear."},{"time":753101,"text":"This is a revolution in astronomy,"},{"time":756672,"text":"like when Galileo invented the telescope."},{"time":760859,"text":"It's like when they added sound\nto silent movies."},{"time":765110,"text":"This is just the beginning."},{"time":769120,"text":"We like to think"},{"time":771500,"text":"that the road to science is very long --\nvery fun, but very long --"},{"time":777791,"text":"and that we, this large,\ninternational community of scientists,"},{"time":784178,"text":"working from many countries,\ntogether as a team,"},{"time":786762,"text":"are helping to build that road;"},{"time":790048,"text":"that we're shedding light --\nsometimes encountering detours --"},{"time":794488,"text":"and building, perhaps,"},{"time":796915,"text":"a highway to the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799931,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801130,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}